{
  "texts": [
    "In all the examples we mentioned, it is possible to encode the objects by (large enough) vectors, and thus, we will often have X ⊆ R d, where R is the set of real numbers.",
    "The set of labels will be denoted by Y.",
    "The most classical examples of supervised learning problems are binary classification and regression.",
    "In binary classification, Y = {0, 1}.",
    "Examples includes spam detection: in this case, objects in X are e-mails, and the label is 1 if the e-mail is a spam, and 0 otherwise."
  ]
}